column5: I got a calendar at Christmas from a co-worker and today it noted this huge musky at the Freshwater Fishing Hall of Fame and Museum in Hayward, Wisconsin.  The mouth is an observation deck  Thought it was pretty cool.  Fishing Museum Giant Musky  Joey

Whoa!  Must be one of those European Pike angler who caught that one...either that or it's photoshop....LOL.  Actually, I think my uncle caught that fish.  It is a cool pic...would be cool to visit there one day.
You'll get one like that next year Hun.... don't get in too big a rush!
I had heard that that fish was caught on Lake of the Woods.
Yes heard the same thing Roy and a bunch of people are challenging the authenticity of the catch. Some say it was foul hooked.
That's what I was thinking too Wayne  With all your PB's  lately Joey, your gonna be aiming for the sky
Go ahead Joey and try to get that one out of a 8" hole.  Regards. Sam
you all have it wrong it was caught on rainy lake by my uncles cousins half brother twice removed

Jeez, that's bigger than Husky the Musky in Kenora!!! But, the next record will come from Georgian Bay or the Larry according to Dr. Casselman, the fellow studying Muskies, the combination of the warmer water and more food leads to a bigger ultimate size.
heard it was a new 4lbs line weight class record
You guys are too much, thanks for the laughs!!!!  Joey
Funny thing .. I heard it was caught on a Duckling !
